  "prompt": "Female Tinder users of Bangalore, the hell do you expect when you write in your profile \"not looking for hook ups\"?",
  "response": "When female Tinder users in Bangalore (or anywhere else) write \"not looking for hookups\" in their profiles, they are generally trying to communicate their intentions clearly and filter out matches who might be seeking casual or short-term encounters. Here are some common expectations behind this statement:\n\n1. **Clarity of Intentions**: They want to attract people who are genuinely interested in meaningful connections, relationships, or friendships rather than casual hookups.\n\n2. **Respect for Boundaries**: They\u2019re signaling their boundaries and hoping potential matches will respect them. It\u2019s a way to avoid wasting time on conversations that might not align with their goals.\n\n3. **Filtering Out Misaligned Matches**: They\u2019re hoping to deter individuals who are primarily on the app for casual encounters, even if they still receive such advances occasionally.\n\n4. **Focus on Compatibility**: They\u2019re likely looking for someone who shares similar values, interests, or goals for the relationship, whether it\u2019s dating, a long-term partnership, or even just meaningful conversations.\n\nThat said, writing \"not looking for hookups\" doesn\u2019t always guarantee the desired outcome. Some users might ignore or misinterpret it, while others may still try to push boundaries. It\u2019s a way to set expectations, but the effectiveness often depends on how seriously others take it.",
